HEADWORD: Hire and purchase agreement
<hw>Hire and purchase
agreement</hw>}</mhw>. <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A contract (more fully
called contract of hire with an option of purchase) in which a person
hires goods for a specified period and at a fixed rent, with the added
condition that if he shall retain the goods for the full period and pay
all the installments of rent as they become due the contract shall
determine and the title vest absolutely in him, and that if he chooses
he may at any time during the term surrender the goods and be quit of
any liability for future installments upon the contract. In the United
States such a contract is generally treated as a conditional sale, and
the term <xex>hire purchase</xex> is also sometimes applied to a
contract in which the hirer is not free to avoid future liability by
surrender of the goods. In England, however, if the hirer does not have
this right the contract is a sale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hirer</ent>⟦br⟧
